RTHS Schedules are now live in Skyward. They look a lot different from the previous year. Please see the attachment for schedule clarity. https://bit.ly/RTHS_Schedule

- Students will have learning expectations days they are not at present for in-person school. Our next post will be about remote (e-learning) expectations. Stay tuned.

- If you have not registered your schedule has been deleted. You will need to call the office to set up an appointment with counselors.

- If you need to talk to your counselor about your schedule, call the main office to set up an appointment.

- New students will be contacted by RTHS to meet with a counselor. They will be allotted 30-minute appointments; returning students 15 get minutes.

- Counselors will see students as follows

- Tuesday, Aug 11 8:30am-noon (last appt at 11:45), 1-4:15 pm (last appt at 4:00) and 5:30-7pm last appt at 6:45)

- Wednesday, Aug 12 8:30am-noon (last appt at 11:45), 1-4pm (last appt at 3:45)

- Thursday, Aug 13, 1-4pm (last appt at 3:45)

RTHS Parking Pass Update
Due to COVID and busing logistics, RTHS encourages students and families to provide their own transportation to school. Please read over our attachment for our transportation policy for busing during the this Pandemic

For the first week of school, students who are driving to school will arrive at the RTHS parking lot and park on a first-come basis in the parking spot of their choice. Students are not permitted to park in the West Parking Lot, or the Northeast back corner of the student parking designated for parent pick up.

Once school starts we will have sign-ups for student assigned parking spots and the fee. Information will be provided in announcements on the first day of classes.

https://bit.ly/RTHSBuspolicy

post_text:
Congratulations MEGAN!!!
2020 Rockford Women's Golf Classic Champion

RTHS senior Megan Thiravong is the champion this year at the Greater Rockford Women's Classic played today at Aldeen Golf Course. Megan defeated two-time champion Hui Chong Dofflemyer 2 and 1 in the match play finals today. It is the first time Thiravong has won the tournament.
Megan was 1 up after 9 holes in the match and 3 up with only 3 holes remaining. She closed out the match after the 17th hole. Thiravong got into the finals following a semi-final win on Saturday against Western Illinois University golfer Natalie Hooper 1 up at Sandy Hollow Golf Course in Rockford.

Congratulations MEGAN!!!
2020 Rockford Women's Golf Classic Champion

Megan was 1 up after 9 holes in the match and 3 up with only 3 holes remaining. She closed out the match after the 17th hole. Thiravong got into the finals following a semi-final win on Saturday against Western Illinois University golfer Natalie Hooper 1 up at Sandy Hollow Golf Course in Rockford.

RTHS UPDATES

RTHS Students and Parents - We understand there are a lot of questions about the 2020-2021 school year. Thank you for your patience during this challenging process. We will be working on communicating with you on a variety of topics and questions that need clarification over the next couple of weeks. Please stay tuned. We want to get the first day of school dates out as they are slightly different from our original schedule.

- The first day of in-person classes for grades 9/10 will be on Monday, August 17

- The first day of in-person classes for grades 11/12 will be on Tuesday, August 18.

- Grades 9/10 will be on Mondays/Wednesdays and every other Friday

- Grades 11/12 will be on Tuesday/Thursdays and every other Friday

- In-person classes will run from 8:05-12:25
KEC classes will begin on Wednesday, August 19.

RFD is on the frontline of this pandemic, but their social organization is still focused on helping the community. With their 2 largest fundraisers of the year cancelled due to coronavirus, they're scrambling to find ways to earn donations to fund their projects (like the RTHS scholarship).

post_text: Congrats to RTHS SRO Deputy Brodzik. Enjoy Retirement.
shared_text:
Ogle County Sheriff's Office
May 28 at 2:37 PM ·

We would like to congratulate Deputy Cheri Brodzik on her retirement after 29 years at the Ogle County Sheriff’s Office. Cheri was a DARE Officer for 13 years of her career, as well as a field training officer on patrol, and she worked in court security. Cheri was the School Resource Officer at the Rochelle Township High School for the last two years. Thank you for your many years of service and dedication to the citizens of Ogle County!

post_text:
Former School Nurse Colleen Esterday gave me permission to share her post with Members of the Class of 2020:

The Senior Class of 2020 my first, first grade class at D231, I believe. The beauty of FB is that I have continued to watch them grow through the years. I loved hugging on them, fixing their boo-boo’s, and getting to know their families. I MISS THEM!

I can’t help but note how many are choosing to go into nursing and other fields of medicine.

I feel like I’ll be in good hands as I/we grow older, and need medical attention (hopefully not, but it will be good to see them succeed).

Congrats Class of 2020! I’m proud of you!

post_text:
La escuela de RTHS está trabajando en soluciones para que nuestros estudiantes continúen aprendiendo mientras las

escuelas se encuentren cerradas. El acceso a la tecnología y a una confiable conexión de internet serán herramientas importantes para el éxito estudiantil despues del 31 de marzo. Mas detalles sobre el plan de RTHS seran compartidos durante las vacaciones de primavera.

Mientras tanto, les instamos a que consideren otras formas para permanecer conectados a la internet en casa. Parece que COMCAST es la mejor opcion para las familias de Rochelle. Por favor, consideren suscribirse por 2 meses de acceso gratis a internet en www.internetessentials.com o use la conexion gratuita de wifi Xfinity para conectar sus aparatos electronicos. Mas detalles pueden encontrarse en hotspots.wifi.xfinity.com.

post_text:
RTHS is working on solutions for our students to continue learning while schools are shut down. Access to technology and a reliable internet connection is going to be important tools for student success after March 31. More details about RTHS’s plan will be shared over Spring Break.

In the meantime, we are urging you to consider ways to get connected to the internet in your household. Comcast seems to be the best option for Rochelle area families. Please consider signing up for 2 months of free internet at www.internetessentials.com or use the free Xfinity wifi network to connect your devices.Details can be found at hotspots.wifi.xfinity.com.

post_text:
School closure extended

The Rochelle Schools is aware that Gov. Pritzker has issued a shelter-in-place order combined with an extended school closure through April 7, 2020 (returning April 8, 2020).

The Rochelle Schools have been preparing for an announcement of this nature. Please expect more specific details about alternative learning assignments and meal distribution early next week.

Continue to check our Facebook and website for evolving details.

Thank you for your patience.

Las Escuelas de Rochelle saben que el gobernador Pritzker emitió una orden de refugio “shelter-in-place” combinada con un cierre prolongado de la escuela hasta el 7 de abril de 2020 (regresando el 8 de abril de 2020). Las Escuelas Rochelle se han estado preparando para un anuncio de esta naturaleza. Espere detalles más específicos sobre las tareas de aprendizaje alternativas y la distribución de comidas a principios de la próxima semana. Continúe revisando nuestro Facebook y sitio web para obtener detalles adicionales. Gracias por su paciencia.

Rochelle Township High School
March 19 at 4:09 PM ·

RTHS Students,

Please fill out this quick survey. You will only be able to fill out this form logging into your RTHS student google account. It is vital you fill it out so that we know how to allocate resources. Please do it by 10 pm tonight. http://bit.ly/2wkxRxT

RTHS is investigating our students' access to a computer and the internet. At this time, we anticipate our return to school to be as scheduled for Tuesday 3/31/20. However, we continue to monitor the CDC, IDPH, and ISBE guidance for schools as it relates to the COVID-19 pandemic and await further direction from the Governor. In the event that the school closure is extended and alternative learning needs to continue, we want to understand what support students may need.

We understand if you don't fill this out, it probably means you do not have access to a computer or the internet.

Take care and stay safe,
